#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:3
#: e6c240c595234c3182c6cc03e6eb2b09
msgid "Privacy policy"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:6
#: 760fb87c6a134fb49a3aee8f522f90bb
msgid "The short version is that we try to respect your privacy as much as possible. We absolutely do not sell any user data. In fact, we go out of our way to help you keep your data private from everyone, including us. For example, from the moment you :doc:`install Qubes OS </user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide>`, we offer to set up `Whonix <https://www.whonix.org/>`__ so that all of your updates are routed through `Tor <https://www.torproject.org/>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:9
#: c6cf4e42ed874a0d892822223ee0de9d
msgid "Website"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:12
#: 9f471a9b5340491daf614e1708a1c167
msgid "For the legally-required boilerplate, see `Website Privacy Policy <https://www.qubes-os.org/website-privacy-policy/>`__."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:14
#: b6d4f8cfd4154448940b2b6ffeb7bd81
msgid "This is just a static website generated with Jekyll and hosted from GitHub Pages. We try to use as little JavaScript as possible. We host all resources locally (no third-party CDNs) so that you only have to connect to one domain. The website should be easy to browse using Tor Browser and with scripts blocked. We also have an `onion service <http://qubesosfasa4zl44o4tws22di6kepyzfeqv3tg4e3ztknltfxqrymdad.onion/>`__ (access is not logged). We even go out of our way to make it easy to download `this website’s git repo <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubesos.github.io>`__, including all the website source code, so that you can host this entire site from your own local machine offline."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:16
#: f220a3105cf442568456caa2cdf8a6ba
msgid "Most of the website is written in Markdown so that the plain text can be enjoyed from the comfort of your terminal. Obviously, we don’t use any ads or trackers, but this is still a public website, so man-in-the-middle attacks and such are always a possibility. Please be careful. See :ref:`FAQ: Should I trust this website? <introduction/faq:should i trust this website?>`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:20
#: 5d40488e37834adc81e33e997301fe31
msgid "Qubes OS documentation"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:22
#: 40141a1eb73f47d68a0f7aff45a14cab
msgid "Qubes OS documentation is hosted on `Read The Docs <https://readsthedocs.com/>`__. We’ve converted all of the :doc:`documentation </index>` from Markdown to reStructuredText. You can enjoy the plain text from the comfort of your terminal. Here’s the `repo <https://github.com/QubesOS/qubes-doc>`__. (By the way, Git tags on our repos are PGP-signed so you can :doc:`verify </project-security/verifying-signatures>` the authenticity of the content.) We omit the ethical ads from RTD, but this is still a public website, so man-in-the-middle attacks and such are always a possibility. Please be careful. Also see :ref:`FAQ: Why is the documentation hosted on ReadTheDocs as opposed to the website? <introduction/faq:why is the documentation hosted on readthedocs as opposed to the website?>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:25
#: 82cf08e4497845be8b3dc1e69c5a6f57
msgid "Please refer to RTD's `privacy policy <https://docs.readthedocs.com/platform/stable/privacy-policy.html>`__ for more information. As per RTD site, the TL;DR version is as follows:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:36
#: 31c3792e0b4b49de8119bc2e259f82eb
msgid "Update Servers and Repositories"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:39
#: 52517e7cbcbf45dc994872fb6759851c
msgid "We provide repositories at https://yum.qubes-os.org and https://deb.qubes-os.org."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:41
#: 409c95191dcb49d8aaa7eaf7c679bc79
msgid "We collect and store standard server access and error logs, which include IP addresses. We use this data for generating :doc:`Qubes userbase statistics </introduction/statistics>` and for incident response."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:43
#: 2167491f4ea14a608a89aa3530852466
msgid "The data is retained for up to three months so that we can re-calculate the previous two months’ statistics in case anything goes wrong. After that, the data is deleted. We never sell the data to anyone or share it with any third party."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:45
#: a754b209628641d7a77b5e5f3cb766f2
msgid "If you would like to hide your IP address from us, we strongly encourage it and are happy to help you do so! Simply choose the Whonix option to route all of your updates over Tor when :doc:`installing Qubes OS </user/downloading-installing-upgrading/installation-guide>`."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:48
#: cd9229dd2a7d497089f0a76fdf04abf5
msgid "Onion Services"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:51
#: 22aef0eb1ccb4902800d626382ee4354
msgid "We provide an `onion service <http://www.qubesosfasa4zl44o4tws22di6kepyzfeqv3tg4e3ztknltfxqrymdad.onion>`__ for the website and onion service mirrors of the repositories. Access to these servers is not logged."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:54
#: 46fe288a38ce47b295ce7dfb70e3a212
msgid "Mirrors"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:57
#: 0a5dcdd5de3547bfa56963faecd3f162
msgid "There are also other third-party mirrors hosted by volunteers. These are used both for `ISO downloads <https://www.qubes-os.org/downloads/#mirrors>`__ and `updates <#update-servers-and-repositories>`__. We have no control over what data these mirrors collect or with whom they share it. Please see the privacy policy of each respective mirror operator."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:60
#: 08748ce1baac4e10a85469a2b5ecf71f
msgid "Qubes OS"
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:63
#: aad18818fe9b4077aa755933e6970f13
msgid "We have specifically designed Qubes OS so that it is not possible to collect any data directly from Qubes OS installations. In other words, Qubes OS does not have the ability to “phone home” and is intentionally architected to forbid that from happening. This is mainly because we have ensured that dom0 has no network access."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:65
#: 0ed24c95f8244491bf75afd288266c2e
msgid "We don’t want the ability to collect any data directly from Qubes OS installations, because if anyone has that power, then the system is not secure. We use Qubes OS ourselves as a daily driver for our work and personal lives, so our interests are aligned with yours. We want privacy too! Thankfully, Qubes OS is free and open-source software, so you don’t have to take our word for it."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:67
#: 42bd3e8c5bf349ff8de0bdd528cb15bb
msgid "Of course, third-party software (including other operating systems) running inside of Qubes OS may not be as privacy-respecting, so please be mindful of what you install. We have no control over such third-party software."
msgstr ""

#: ../../introduction/privacy.rst:69
#: 3330bf7d678d4d7c98a40cfd0582fdb7
msgid "For more information, please see :ref:`FAQ: How does Qubes OS provide privacy? <introduction/faq:how does qubes os provide privacy?>`"
msgstr ""
